<item>
            <title>[MATH-1376] SimplexOptimizer.doOptimize(): Wrong Iteration Number (0) Passed to Convergence Checker</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1376</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The convergence checker used in method doOptimize() of SimplexOptimizer always receives 0 as iteration counter. This can very easily be fixed. Check this out:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Original (with added comments):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; iteration = 0; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// XXXXXXXXX set to zero and never update
&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; ConvergenceChecker&amp;lt;PointValuePair&amp;gt; checker = getConvergenceChecker();
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (getIterations() &amp;gt; 0) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; converged = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i = 0; i &amp;lt; simplex.getSize(); i++) {
                    PointValuePair prev = previous[i];
                    converged = converged &amp;amp;&amp;amp; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// XXXXXXXXX ouch below
&lt;/span&gt;                        checker.converged(iteration, prev, simplex.getPoint(i));
                }
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (converged) {
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// We have found an optimum.
&lt;/span&gt;                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; simplex.getPoint(0);
                }
            }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;should be (with added comments)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; iteration = 0;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; ConvergenceChecker&amp;lt;PointValuePair&amp;gt; checker = getConvergenceChecker();
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;) {
            iteration = getIterations(); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// XXXXXXXX CHANGE 1
&lt;/span&gt;            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (iteration &amp;gt; 0) {  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// XXXXXXXX CHANGE 2
&lt;/span&gt;                &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; converged = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i = 0; i &amp;lt; simplex.getSize(); i++) {
                    PointValuePair prev = previous[i];
                    converged = converged &amp;amp;&amp;amp;
                        checker.converged(iteration, prev, simplex.getPoint(i));
                }
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (converged) {
                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// We have found an optimum.
&lt;/span&gt;                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; simplex.getPoint(0);
                }
            }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
